    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proclamation No. 2463, Signed by President Roosevelt, March 4,
                        1941</hi>
                    <note n="48" type="source" xml:id="d171fn48">Reprinted from Department of State,
                            <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, March 8, 1941 (vol. <hi
                            rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, No. 89), p. 243.</note>
                </head>
                <p>Whereas section 6 of the act of Congress entitled “<hi rend="smallcaps">An Act
                        To</hi> expedite the strengthening of the national defense,” approved July
                    2, 1940, provides as follows:</p>
                <p>[Here follows the text of the act as quoted in proclamation No. 2413 of July 2,
                    1940, printed on <ref target="#pg_211">page 211</ref>.]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Now, therefore, I, Franklin D. Roosevelt</hi>, President of
                    the United States of America, acting under and by virtue of the authority vested
                    in me by the aforesaid act of Congress, do hereby proclaim that upon the
                    recommendation of the Administrator of Export Control I have determined that it
                    is necessary in the interest of the national defense that on and after March 10,
                    1941, the following-described articles and materials shall not be exported from
                    the United States except when authorized in each case by a license as <pb
                        facs="0319" n="253" xml:id="pg_253"/> provided for in Proclamation No. 2413
                    of July 2, 1940, entitled “Administration of section 6 of the Act entitled ‘<hi
                        rend="smallcaps">An Act To</hi> expedite the strengthening of the national
                    defense’ approved July 2, 1940”: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Cadmium</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Carbon Black</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>Coconut Oil</item>
                        <label>(4)</label>
                        <item>Copra</item>
                        <label>(5)</label>
                        <item>Cresylic Acid and Cresols</item>
                        <label>(6)</label>
                        <item>Fatty Acids produced from vegetable oils under export control</item>
                        <label>(7)</label>
                        <item>Glycerin</item>
                        <label>(8)</label>
                        <item>Palm-Kernel Oil and Palm Kernels</item>
                        <label>(9)</label>
                        <item>Pine Oil</item>
                        <label>(10)</label>
                        <item>Petroleum Coke</item>
                        <label>(11)</label>
                        <item>Shellac</item>
                        <label>(12)</label>
                        <item>Titanium</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">In witness whereof</hi>, I have hereunto set my hand and
                    caused the seal of the United States of America to be affixed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <seg type="margin">[<hi rend="smallcaps">seal</hi>]</seg>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Done</hi> at the city of
                            <placeName>Washington</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian us-republic" when="1941-03-04">this 4th day of
                            March, in the year of our Lord nineteen hundred and forty-one, and of
                            the Independence of the United States of America, the one hundred and
                            sixty-fifth</date>.</dateline>
                    <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin D. Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>By the President:<lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
